						               													<description>Do you have the nerve, the skill and the derring-do to challenge the wind and play PERIL OF THE POLE?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a board game which comes with Philip Pullman's book &amp;quot;Once Upon a Time in the North&amp;quot;, the fifth book in the His Dark Materials series.  &amp;#10;The board game is kept in a tuck pocket inside the back cover.  It includes a board with printed instructions on the reverse, and a card which contains a Wind Compass and 6 player Balloon tokens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a simple Roll-and-Move Children's game depicting competing aeronaughts seeking to survive the longest in the North Pole; the winner is decided by the last player not destroyed in the Polar Maelstrom.  The game requires a Die which is not included.  The Wind Compass is used to decide which direction the player's Balloon moves to when it lands on an appropriate space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a presented in an antique style in keeping with the general design of the period depicted in the books.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
